modules.description: This module provides functions to construct inline and block-level elements of a document, such as text, emphasis, links, paragraphs, lists, headings, and code blocks. It works with abstract syntax tree (AST) structures representing document elements, using tuples for attributes and lists for content. Concrete use cases include building structured Markdown documents programmatically, generating HTML output from custom data, and embedding raw HTML fragments within a document.

This module parses Markdown into an abstract syntax tree and converts it to HTML or S-expressions, supporting document construction, table of contents generation, and HTML escaping. It provides direct access to block and inline element manipulation, allowing operations like extracting structured content or rendering static websites. The child module enables programmatic creation of document elements such as headings, lists, links, and code blocks, using tuples for attributes and lists for content. Together, they support tasks like generating HTML from custom data structures or embedding raw HTML fragments within a Markdown document.
